Cell.Text: [S] Now that you've transacted the Oath, it's time to reveal the final piece of the puzzle to you; Mercer's true crime.

Node.ToolTip:
0005AE99 - Custom, in use by ananes
Last User:ananes Date:4/18/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: Mercer was able to unlock the Guild's vault without two keys because of what he stole from the Twilight Sepulcher... the Skeleton Key. | By doing this, he's compromised our ties to Nocturnal and in essence, caused our luck run dry.

Node.Caption: TG08AKarliahPostOathBranchTopic01a: He's done more?

Node.ToolTip:
0005AE98 - Custom, in use by ananes
Last User:ananes Date:4/18/2011 File:Skyrim.esm

Cell.Text: Well, yes. But the Key isn't only restricted to physical barriers. | All of us possess untapped abilities; the potential to weild great power, securely sealed within our minds. | Once you realize the Key can access these traits, the potential becomes limitless.

Node.Caption: TG08AKarliahPostOathBranchTopic02: So the Key unlocks any door?

Cell.Text: Although it would benefit the Guild more than you can imagine, in the end, it would do more harm than good.

Node.Caption: TG08AKarliahPostOathBranchTopic03a: The Guild should possess this item.
TG08AKarliahPostOathBranchTopic03b: The three of us could keep it.

Cell.Text: Good, then you understand why this is about more than just Mercer's lust for power.

Node.Caption: TG08AKarliahPostOathBranchTopic3c: Sounds like no one should possess it.

Cell.Text: Very true. In our line of work, it's quite rare we set out to return a stolen item to its rightful owner.

Node.Caption: TG08AKarliahOutroExtBranchTopic: First time I ever set out to return something...

Cell.Text: [S] If the Key isn't returned to its lock in the Twilight Sepulcher, things will never be the same for the Guild. | As time passed, our luck would diminish to the point of non-existence. And whether you know it or not, our uncanny luck defines our trade.
[S] Before we depart, Brynjolf has some business to discuss. I suggest you listen to him.
